Singer Paulina Gagarina named helping to lose weight
Russian singer Polina Gagarina named five products that helped her adjust her figure and subsequently not gain weight again.
Water was first on the list.
The singer prefers to drink clean, non-carbonated water before each meal to dull feelings of hunger and eat less.
Vegetable salad, brown rice and seafood are also ideal for keeping slim.
They can create a balanced diet: vegetables contain fiber, rice has complex carbohydrates, and seafood is a source of protein, healthy vitamins and amino acids.
For unloading days, the singer chooses apples.
With these products, Gagarina was able to get rid of 30 extra kilos.
In addition, the singer switched to fractional eating - eating often and little by little and eliminated fat, sweet and calorie from her diet.
Gagarina does not eat fried food, pastries, sausages and other meat semis, kp.ru writes July 26.
It also replaced fish and seafood red meat.
Prefers vegetables (except potatoes), wholegrain cereals and lots of greens.
Also, Gagarina is active in gym, yoga and running.
